tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: Laboratory results are largely within normal limits. Notable findings include mildly decreased creatinine, likely reflecting low muscle mass rather than renal dysfunction in this elderly patient, and elevated total cholesterol, which may increase cardiovascular risk. Glucose control and renal markers are unremarkable. No evidence of significant proteinuria. Recommend clinical correlation and consideration of lipid management if appropriate.
